 <item> <title>Michigan to Receive Nearly $430 Million in Additional Recovery Funds</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/michigan-receive-nearly-430-million-additional-recovery-funds</link>
 <description> U. S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan today announced that an additional $429,781,767 is now available for Michigan under the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act (ARRA) of 2009.  To date, Michigan has received $2,765,006,656 through the Recovery Act. The state recently reported that recovery dollars have been used to provide funding for more than 9,300 education jobs from Oct. 1 to Dec.</description>
